definition: to interweave
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]
to weave/to knit
mixture of love and hate

sentences.english: Area Serai, intertwined vines and plant species richness.
sentences.chinese: 景區林鬱蒼蘢，藤蔓交織，植物物種豐富。

sentences.english: A diagonal interleave method is proposed based on the distance properties of Turbo codes.
sentences.chinese: 根據碼距特性提出了對角交織的優化交織法。

sentences.english: A diagonal interleave method is proposed based on the distance properties of Turbo codes.
sentences.chinese: 根據碼距特性提出了對角交織的優化交織法。

sentences.english: This is Iceland, a land of fire and ice.
sentences.chinese: 這就是冰島，一個冰火交織的極致王國。

sentences.english: The melt of slim yellow and pink is deducing the subject of love forever.
sentences.chinese: 昏黃與粉色調的交織，輕輕演繹永久不變的愛的主題。

sentences.english: Americans have always had an ambivalent attitude toward  intelligence.
sentences.chinese: 美國人對情報工作有種愛恨交織態度。

sentences.english: At first he removes it and mingles with the children.
sentences.chinese: 起初，他刪除，並與孩子交織在一起。

sentences.english: In the story,truth was interweaved with fiction.
sentences.chinese: 這篇故事中，真實與虛構交織在一起。

sentences.english: Hopes and fears chequer human life .
sentences.chinese: 人生由希望和憂愁交織而成。

sentences.english: The aggregate quantity contradiction and the structural contradiction interlaces each other in the employment in China at present.
sentences.chinese: 當前我國就業中總量性矛盾與結構性矛盾相互交織。

sentences.english: Beauty and sexuality have become so completely intertwined as to be indistinguishable.
sentences.chinese: 現在的所謂美麗與性感往往交織在一起，很難辨別。

sentences.english: That is because they are often closely interwoven.
sentences.chinese: 那是因爲他們常常緊密地交織在一起。
驚異和喜悅交織在一起。

sentences.english: A jagged scar runs down his forehead.
sentences.chinese: 他的額頭上交織着累累疤痕。

sentences.english: In this thesis, I use convolutional interleaving technology.
sentences.chinese: 本文采用了卷積交織技術。
